arcade.patch.agent.cell

Class PatchCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.patch.agent.cell.PatchCell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cell, java.io.Serializable, sim.engine.Steppable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PatchCellTissue

    public abstract class PatchCell
extends java.lang.Object
implements Cell
    Implementation of Cell for generic tissue cell.

    PatchCell agents exist in one of seven states: undefined, apoptotic, quiescent, migratory, proliferative, senescent, and necrotic. The undefined state is a transition state for "undecided" cells, and does not have any biological analog.

    PatchCell agents have two required Process domains: metabolism and signaling. Metabolism controls changes in cell energy and volume. Signaling controls the proliferative vs. migratory decision.

    General order of rules for the PatchCell step:

    • update age
    • check lifespan (possible change to apoptotic)
    • step metabolism process
    • check energy status (possible change to quiescent or necrotic depending on ENERGY_THRESHOLD)
    • step signaling process
    • check if neutral (change to proliferative, migratory, senescent)
    • step state-specific module

    Cells that become necrotic or senescent have a change to become apoptotic instead (NECROTIC_FRACTION and SENESCENT_FRACTION, respectively).

    Cell parameters are tracked using a map between the parameter name and value. Daughter cell parameter values are drawn from a distribution centered on the parent cell parameter with the specified amount of heterogeneity (HETEROGENEITY).

      • PatchCell

        public PatchCell(int id,
                 int parent,
                 int pop,
                 Enums.State state,
                 int age,
                 int divisions,
                 Location location,
                 MiniBox parameters,
                 double volume,
                 double height,
                 double criticalVolume,
                 double criticalHeight)
        Creates a PatchCell agent.

        Loaded parameters include:

        • NECROTIC_FRACTION = fraction of necrotic cells that become apoptotic
        • SENESCENT_FRACTION = fraction of senescent cells that become apoptotic
        • ENERGY_THRESHOLD = maximum energy deficit before necrosis
        • HETEROGENEITY = variation in cell agent parameters
        Parameters:
        id - the cell ID
        parent - the parent ID
        pop - the cell population index
        state - the cell state
        age - the cell age
        divisions - the number of cell divisions
        location - the Location of the cell
        parameters - the dictionary of parameters
        volume - the cell volume
        height - the cell height
        criticalVolume - the critical cell volume
        criticalHeight - the critical cell height
